[2] American Samoa: Measles Outbreaks Situational Report
Date: Mon 30 Dec 2019
Source: Government of American Samoa [abridged, edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/american-samoa/american-samoa-measles-outbreaks-situational-report-december-15-28-2019


Total number of cases to date: 10 laboratory-confirmed via RT-PCR testing at Hawaii State Lab; 4 suspected cases with laboratory results pending; measles transmission only on the island of Tutuila.

- Rash onset date for last laboratory confirmed measles case: 7 Dec 2019. Outbreak Declaration will be lifted after 2 incubation periods (42 days from 7 Dec 2019) without another laboratory confirmed case.

- American Samoa continues its campaign to vaccinate all school aged children. About 98% of children (12 months -- 18 years old) with 1st dose of MMR, and 90% of children (4 -- 18 years old) have completed 2 recommended doses of MMR.

- 11 Dec 2019 American Samoa began its campaign to vaccinate all adults with no evidence of MMR vaccine. To date 12 932 MMR doses administered (780 doses to children 6 months -- 18 years old; 12 152 doses to adults 19 years and older).

- American Samoa continues to restrict entry at its borders from travelers via Samoa and Tonga. Travel permits will require a 15-day review process. Proof of immunity against measles is required for entry from these locations.

- The ban of all public gatherings has been lifted, effective 16 Dec 2019

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

